Global Metal Waste Recycling Equipment Market Insights
Metal Waste Recycling Equipment Market size was valued at USD 8.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 12.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Metal Waste Recycling Equipment Market Overview
The global metal waste recycling equipment market is valued at approximately USD 12.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to reach USD 18.9 billion by 2032, growing at a CAGR of 5.5% during the forecast period. This market growth is driven by the increasing demand for efficient recycling processes and the rising need for sustainable waste management practices. The equipment used in this market includes shredders, crushers, compactors, and sorting machines, which are integral for reducing the volume of metal waste and improving recycling rates. The market is further supported by innovations in recycling technology and rising government regulations promoting recycling practices.

